<p>I am making a carousel of several objects. It is supposed to spin the carousel, so the next object is in focus, when I click the next/previous buttons. The first time I click one of the buttons, it slowly animates the spin, but with the next clicks it just changes object without animation for some reason. And it should animate everytime i click, but it does it only the first time after each page reload.</p>  <p>Here is a jsfiddle: <a href="https://jsfiddle.net/sxybreak/jouevx28/1/" rel="nofollow">https://jsfiddle.net/sxybreak/jouevx28/1/</a></p>  <p>Here is my code:</p>  <pre><code>$(document).ready(function() {     var angle;     var i = 0;      $("#previous").on('click', function() {          i+=1;          $("#carousel").animate({borderSpacing: 40}, {             duration: 'slow',              step: function(now, fx) {                  $(this).css({                'transform': 'rotateY(' + (i*now) + 'deg)',                '-webkit-transform': 'rotateY(' + (i*now) + 'deg)',                '-moz-transform': 'rotateY(' + (i*now) + 'deg)',                '-ms-transform': 'rotateY(' + (i*now) + 'deg)' });         }      });   });     $("#next").click(function() {      i-=1;      $("#carousel").animate({borderSpacing: 40}, {       duration: 'slow',       step: function(now, fx) {          $(this).css({             'transform': 'rotateY(' + (i*now) + 'deg)',             '-webkit-transform': 'rotateY(' + (i*now) + 'deg)',             '-moz-transform': 'rotateY(' + (i*now) + 'deg)',             '-ms-transform': 'rotateY(' + (i*now) + 'deg)' });       }     });   }); }); </code></pre>